  "texts": [
    "Model performance was then calculated taking the median consistency rate (CR median) from all CR scores.",
    "• Semantic Consistency (SC) denotes whether the generated notes contextually mean the same regardless of how they were written across all iterations per transcript.",
    "This was measured by calculating the BERTScore which is an automatic text generation evaluation metric that calculates the cosine similarity between a pair of notes in the contextual embedding space (Zhang et al., 2020), using the implementation in Hugging Face.",
    "The pairs of notes refer to all combinations of the ten (10) generated notes per transcript.",
    "To determine model performance, the median semantic consistency SC median was then calculated by getting the median of all semantic consistency scores calculated per transcript."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This was measured by calculating the BERTScore which is an automatic text generation evaluation metric that calculates the cosine similarity between a pair of notes in the contextual embedding space (Zhang et al., 2020), using the implementation in Hugging Face."
